  "text": "This example is an implementation of the phase estimation algorithm as a subroutine of the randomised order finding algorithm, in order to illustrate the use of constructors for controlled operators. The order finding algorithm computes the order 21 r of x with respect to N , where x and N are two coprime integer variables with x < N . The phase estimation subroutine is used to return a mantissa which approximates s/r where s is a random number in [0, . . . , r − 1]. The result is to be passed through the continued fraction algorithm (which is completely classical) in order to extract r. The interested reader can find further details in [CITATION_1] .",
